  "description": "New Operations Center Phase 2",
  "enriched_description": "Continuation of GUC's strategic relocation from flood-prone Mumford Road (damaged in Hurricane Floyd 1999) to new 82-acre hardened campus at NC 43 / US 264 Bypass. Phase 1 completed Sept 2020: $43M campus with 157,000 SF across 3 buildings + 2 storage facilities, built by Barnhill. Features tornado-resistant construction, heavy-duty steel, 24/7 Station 1 monitoring center for all utilities. 69% local spend ($29.7M to Pitt County businesses, 100+ jobs). Fleet Building ($7.75M, 22,600 SF, 653 fleet assets) completed 2022. Old Mumford Road property (12 parcels) declared surplus and marketed for sale - potential redevelopment opportunity. Phase 2 continues campus buildout.",
